Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and discard root end from
@baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop into bite-size pieces. Thinly slice
@scallions{2}. Crush @peanuts{1/2%oz} in their bag.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; dice into
bite-size pieces and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz},
@mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, juice from half the lime, @olive oil{2%tbsp},
@sugar{1/2%tsp}, a big pinch of salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use juice from whole lime, 4 TBSP olive oil, and 1 tsp sugar.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together lettuce, scallions, @shredded carrots{4%oz},
and half the dressing. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Add chicken to bowl with remaining dressing and toss to coat.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with chicken and garnish with peanuts.
Tear @cilantro{1/4%oz} with your hands and sprinkle over salad.
Serve with remaining lime wedges.